05/11/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- The death toll from heavy rains and floods in southeast Turkey rose to 40 on Friday (November 3rd), according to local media reports.
They cited information from regional authorities in Mardin, Batman, Sirnak and Mersin that said that floods claimed seven more lives, including two children.
At least six people remain missing.
(Zaman, Cihan - 04/11/06;
AP - 03/11/06)
